# Bymed customer website — brand colors and theme

Use these for all **bymed-web** (Next.js storefront) UI work unless the user specifies otherwise.

## Brand palette (from ByMed Medical & Scientific logo)

- **Primary brand blue:** saturated royal blue, canonical token `#0000CC` (`--brand-primary` in light theme). Use for primary actions, key navigation, and brand emphasis.
- **On-primary / logo text:** `#FFFFFF`.
- **Depth / shadow / strong borders:** `#000000` (use sparingly; prefer semantic tokens below).

## Light and dark mode

- The storefront **must** support **light** and **dark** themes for accessibility and user preference.
- Implement with **`next-themes`** + Tailwind **`darkMode: "class"`** + CSS variables in `bymed-web/app/globals.css`.
- In **dark** theme, the primary blue may be **slightly lighter or adjusted** than `#0000CC` so contrast on near-black backgrounds meets WCAG for text and controls; keep the same brand character.

## Source of truth in code

Canonical variable definitions live in **`bymed-web/app/globals.css`** (`:root` and `.dark`). Tailwind maps them via **`bymed-web/tailwind.config.ts`**. Do not hardcode one-off hex values in components when a token exists.
